name: Greenyard Restaurant & Bar

reviews.review_text:
Good food but price are bit high..if place is crowded then your order will  get delayed for suree

We tried their almost all chicken dishes

1.chicken muglai
2.chicken kholapuri
3.pepper chicken is must try
4.crispy chicken
5.chicken fried rice
6.chicken pakora
7.chicken manchao soup
8.masala papad
9.green salad
10.chapati
11.lime soda

It was very disappointed the day we went tandoori counter was not available

This is located near Basilica church and Museum. Food tasted good. Chicken tikka was good. But Service was bad because they served expired beer. Atmosphere is below average as only some tourists or locals might come here. This is not a very happening place like one expects in Goa.

A guest actually recommended this place for goan food. Yesterday we went there for lunch.
The restaurant is right outside St. Cajetan Church.
We ordered the fish thali with king fish for 1 and pomfret for the other.
It took a little while for the food to arrive. It was hot, freshly prepared and tasty. They also serve green vegetables. Yesterday it was bhendi. Also the tisrio was amazing. The Masala was just right. Not too spicy.
I would definitely recommend this place for visitors who come to Old Goa.

description:
### Greenyard Restaurant & Bar: A Culinary Oasis in Goa

Tucked away near the historic Basilica of Bom Jesus in Old Goa, Greenyard Restaurant & Bar has carved out a niche for itself, earning an impressive rating of 4 from 796 reviewers. This establishment serves as a delightful stop for both locals and tourists craving authentic Goan flavors. With tags reflecting its specialties—such as "Goan," "seafood," and "food quality"—the restaurant showcases a vibrant culinary palette that has garnered attention for its diverse offerings.

### Ambiance & Design

Upon arriving at Greenyard, guests are greeted by a modest yet inviting atmosphere. The restaurant exudes a casual charm, with rustic décor that captures the essence of Goan culture. Subdued lighting enhances the relaxed environment, making it a pleasant spot for a leisurely meal. The proximity to the renowned St. Cajetan Church further adds to its allure, serving as an excellent backdrop for an enjoyable dining experience. Based on customer photos, the dining space displays a mix of traditional and modern elements, creating an approachable yet distinctive vibe.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

Greenyard’s menu is a celebration of Goan cuisine, prominently featuring seafood and chicken dishes. The fish thali, praised by guests, showcases the restaurant's commitment to fresh ingredients and traditional preparation methods. Reviewers rave about the kingfish and pomfret options, highlighting the perfectly balanced masalas that accompany the seafood.

Chicken enthusiasts will not be disappointed either, with an extensive range of dishes—like the must-try pepper chicken, chicken Mughlai, and crispy chicken—taking center stage. The food is noted for its generous portions and vibrant presentation, with a colorful array of salads and sides complementing the main dishes. Guests have commented on the quality of ingredients, although some raised concerns regarding pricing and occasional wait times during peak hours.

### Customer Experience & Service

The service at Greenyard Restaurant & Bar appears to be a mixed bag based on various feedback. While some diners appreciate the friendly staff and the quality of food, others noted inefficiencies, particularly during busy times, leading to delays in service. A concerning report about expired beer being served has raised eyebrows regarding quality control, though it seems to be an outlier rather than a common occurrence.

The restaurant's location does lend itself to fluctuating crowds, and while it's a popular choice among some visitors, others felt it lacked the vibrancy typically associated with Goan dining. That said, those in the know seem to recommend it, especially for those wanting to soak in the local culture and savor authentic dishes.

### Popularity & Reviews

Greenyard has garnered a solid reputation and a loyal following, largely due to mouthwatering recommendations and its proximity to tourist attractions. Reviewers frequently direct newcomers to the restaurant, solidifying its status as a go-to spot for traditional Goan fare. The buzz on social media reflects this endorsement, highlighting signature dishes and inviting tourists to explore its offerings while visiting Old Goa.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The restaurant's appeal is further enhanced through visuals shared by customers. Photographs reveal vibrant plate presentations, showcasing colorful thalis and well-prepared dishes that tempt the palate. The atmosphere captured in the images portrays a space that is both welcoming and comfortable, making it a suitable choice for casual meals or special occasions alike.

In conclusion, Greenyard Restaurant & Bar stands out as a worthwhile dining destination for those venturing into Goa. With its commendable rating, diverse menu, and historic surroundings, it invites customers to indulge in the rich flavors of the region, all while providing a touch of local charm. However, diners may want to be mindful of potential service inconsistencies and plan their visits accordingly to ensure the best experience possible.
